reviewText:
One movie out of three was good; Jack Nicholson was excellent in, "Crossing Guard"
The Al Pacino movie wasn't good.  The one with Liam Neeson was just okay.
Movies not as good as expected.

Bought this for The Crossing Guard.  All actors show up credibly in this emotional piece about more than one form of loss/grief.  David Morse is a favorite of mine who is not in enough films and stands out in this film .  I look forward to seeing the other two films.  Can't believe I missed them in the past.

I watched the Crossing Guard, then People I Know, and finally the Deception
which seemed to be the movies getting better with each one.
Really like Liam Neeson films. I enjoyed seeing this movie again and am glad to add it to my collection.
Three great movies with some of Hollywood's top actors. Very entertaining and lots of suspense. I watched this Miramax triple feature on a rainy day with my family and we all enjoyed it.
